From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 12:58:20 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: add participant bias-judging tutorial page

- New /tutorial route (participant-protected) that walks through 13
  static sample sentences, one at a time, using the same category
  labeling UI as the judge queue.
- Sample sentences + reference bias labels live in
  frontend/src/data/tutorialData.json -- swap in real data there.
- After the last sentence, shows a results screen: overall accuracy,
  per-category accuracy, and a per-sentence review highlighting any
  mismatched categories.
- Added 'Tutorial' link to the participant navbar on Submit and
  Dashboard pages.
